      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted E46 M3, powered by the iconic S54B32 3.2L inline-six engine. This high-compression unit features individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure Double VANOS variable valve timing system, delivering exceptional throttle response up to its 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing M-variable differential lock. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including a documented rod bearing service and a comprehensive rear subframe reinforcement to mitigate floor pan fatigue. The chassis is further refined with polyurethane bushings and Bilstein monotube dampers, providing superior roll stiffness and rebound control. A transparent service history confirms regular valve lash adjustments and cooling system refreshes, making this a robust choice for the discerning enthusiast.",
